routeIdea:
My idea is a route for "Grand Canyon Rim-to-Rim", which is real world.
The  pitch for this route is "A challenging trek across the Grand Canyon, from the North Rim to the South Rim, showcasing breathtaking views of the canyon's vast expanse and geological wonders.".
Some ideas for steps are: 
	 - North Kaibab Trailhead to Cottonwood Campground
	 - Cottonwood Campground to Phantom Ranch
	 - Phantom Ranch to Bright Angel Campground
	 - Bright Angel Campground to Indian Garden
	 - Indian Garden to South Rim

itinerary.startingLocationDescription: The North Kaibab Trailhead is located at the North Rim of the Grand Canyon, offering stunning views and access to the trail.
itinerary.endingLocationDescription: Cottonwood Campground is a popular stop for hikers, providing a place to rest and refill water.
possibleAddressInfo: North Rim, Grand Canyon National Park, AZ
itinerary.anyExtraInformationOnHowToFind: Follow the North Kaibab Trail from the trailhead.

itinerary.startingLocationDescription: Cottonwood Campground offers a serene environment with basic amenities for hikers.
itinerary.endingLocationDescription: Phantom Ranch is a historic lodge located at the bottom of the Grand Canyon, accessible only by foot, mule, or raft.
possibleAddressInfo: Bottom of the Grand Canyon, AZ
itinerary.anyExtraInformationOnHowToFind: Continue on the North Kaibab Trail towards the Colorado River.

itinerary.startingLocationDescription: Phantom Ranch provides a unique lodging experience with cabins and dormitory-style accommodations.
itinerary.endingLocationDescription: Bright Angel Campground is located near the Colorado River, offering a scenic spot for camping.
possibleAddressInfo: Near Colorado River, Grand Canyon National Park, AZ
itinerary.anyExtraInformationOnHowToFind: Head towards the Bright Angel Trail from Phantom Ranch.

itinerary.startingLocationDescription: Bright Angel Campground is a popular resting spot for hikers traversing the canyon.
itinerary.endingLocationDescription: Indian Garden is an oasis halfway up the Bright Angel Trail, offering shade and water.
possibleAddressInfo: Bright Angel Trail, Grand Canyon National Park, AZ
itinerary.anyExtraInformationOnHowToFind: Follow the Bright Angel Trail upwards from the campground.

itinerary.startingLocationDescription: Indian Garden provides a refreshing stop with lush vegetation and a water source.
itinerary.endingLocationDescription: The South Rim is the most accessible part of the Grand Canyon, offering numerous amenities and breathtaking views.
possibleAddressInfo: South Rim, Grand Canyon National Park, AZ
itinerary.anyExtraInformationOnHowToFind: Continue on the Bright Angel Trail to reach the South Rim.
